cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.GR 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks related to face frontalization, which involves synthesizing frontal views of faces from profile views. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also extensively uses deep learning techniques to achieve its goals, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel texture warping procedure and uses dense correspondence fields, which are related to image processing and computer graphics, respectively, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.GR (Graphics) also possible sub-categories.
